New Ebola Virus Cases Reported in Uganda, Daily Monitor Newspaper Says

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-05-24T04:56:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/new-ebola-virus-cases-reported-in-uganda-daily-monitor-newspaper-says.html
Ugandan health authorities are
treating two soldiers of suspected Ebola, bringing the number to
four since a girl died two weeks ago, the Daily Monitor
reported.  The patients are receiving treatment at a hospital near
where the outbreak occurred, while 25 people who came into
contact with the dead girl are being monitored, the Kampala-
based newspaper reported, citing Anthony Mbonye, the 
director general of  health services  at the ministry of health.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
